projectInfo.name: Missing Maps: Buildings in Mandoul, Chad (1)
projectInfo.shortDescription: MSF needs better mapping in the Chad regions of Koumra and Goundi to improve their response to a recent yellow fever outbreak, and for other ongoing and future public health operations in the area.
projectInfo.description: MSF needs better mapping in the Chad regions of Koumra and Goundi to improve their response to a recent yellow fever outbreak, and for other ongoing and future public health operations in the area.
projectInfo.instructions:
**Imagery** 
========================
Please use **Maxar Premium** imagery to map and validate. It is the most recent.

If there is a misalignment between the imagery and the existing data, please do align the existing data with the imagery before you start mapping. You can do that in iD editor by selecting the features that need aligning (Hold down shift + left click on each building), pressing down the shortcut M while moving the mouse to align as closely as possible with the background image, and left click once they are in place. Do not forget to save the changes just as with new buildings. 

Buildings
=========================
Please map all buildings. Buildings are generally squared and round huts with straw or tin roofs. They are **sometimes not easy to spot**, so please scan the area very carefully. But be aware, don't confuse them with trees and rocks!

**For rectangular buildings:** 
* In iD: draw an area and label it as **Building**, then correct for right angles with the **Q** key.
* In JOSM: draw an area and use the tag **building=yes**, then correct for right angles using the **Q** key - OR use the building plugin.

**For circular buildings:** 
* In iD: draw a triangular area over the building and use the tag **Building**, then correct to make the shape circular with the **O** key.
* In JOSM: draw a line on the diameter of the building and use the tag **building=yes**, then hit **Shift+O** to make the shape circular - OR use the building plugin. 

Residential areas, roads and other features
========================
You are **not requested** to map anything other than buildings in this project. If you are mapping in iD your preset tag is Building. However, if there are existing residential areas that do not encompass all the buildings, you can extend them to encompass the more recently built buildings by clicking on the nearest nodes in the residential area border and moving them out, beyond the buildings.  If you are mapping in JOSM and choose to map other features, please check the [Highway Africa Tag page](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Highway_Tag_Africa) for advice on tagging roads and see [the OSM map features page](http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Map_Features) for more information on general OSM tagging.

@[Joram Melissant] Thank you for contributing here. On the overall good job.

There is room for improvement:

- in this task 14 buildings were missing.

- please take care to follow the outline of the roof as close as possible and avoid to oversize the buildings. 
The humanitarian teams use the size of the buildings to estimate the number of people living there. This helps them to work out the approximate total population in the area and how much equipment or medication to bring with them. Buildings that are too big do not fit in with these calculations and lead to inaccuracies in the population count.

Example of your mapping:

![image](https://cdn.hotosm.org/tasking-manager/uploads/1671008426345_2022-12-14-095303-java-openstreetmap-editor.png)

Now resized to the outline of the roof without including the shadow of the building:

![image](https://cdn.hotosm.org/tasking-manager/uploads/1671008482740_2022-12-14-100005-java-openstreetmap-editor.png)

- avoid to map objects on ground level without a roof visible as building

Example of your mapping

![image](https://cdn.hotosm.org/tasking-manager/uploads/1671008576972_2022-12-14-095343-java-openstreetmap-editor.png)

there are no buildings there:

![image](https://cdn.hotosm.org/tasking-manager/uploads/1671008608797_2022-12-14-095350-java-openstreetmap-editor.png)

- do not map separate buildings as 1 building, zoom in close enough, look for the shadow lines and for the roof outline and color

example of your mapping

![image](https://cdn.hotosm.org/tasking-manager/uploads/1671008683628_2022-12-14-095400-java-openstreetmap-editor.png)

now split in 2 separate buildings and a missing one added:

![image](https://cdn.hotosm.org/tasking-manager/uploads/1671008736983_2022-12-14-100005-java-openstreetmap-editor.png)

Don't worry all was fixed. Please take care in the future. Zoom in at 20m or lower and carefully scan the whole task.

Keep mapping.

Please keep in mind these rules when mapping:
Buildings should be squared or have right corners when reasonable. (Shortcut "Q"). Here is an video explanation: https://youtu.be/Xs5wX592E1o
Building should never share nodes with other buildings unless they are physically connected and  building should never share nodes with roads, paths or residential areas. Here is an video explanation: https://youtu.be/ltn1VOiq5_0
When buildings are very close, try to map them close to each other without letting them connect or share nodes with each other, roads or residential area outlines. In the iD editor, holding down the "alt" key will keep nodes of "snapping" to each other and accidentally connecting.
